        SINGAPORE B5 THE STRAITS TIMES SATURDAY, JANUARY 2, 2021 | | | Parenting. A monthly video series organised by
The Straits Times and the National Library Board you ask, we answer, come listen Making movies on your phone Struggling with the terrible twos? Dreading the PSLE? Concerned about college? Millions of us have access to a movie studio. Using a smartphone, you can shoot, edit and publish your own films – and you don’t need a large crew or a huge budget to make it happen. We can help. If you want to enhance holiday videos or save money on a video to promote your business, this session is for you. EMTM video creative director Jonathan Roberts takes you through the basics of how to unleash your inner Spielberg and make movies on your phone. Available every Monday, ST Smart Parenting has articles, videos and podcasts to help you through the many stages of being a parent. Have a question for him? Send it to Check out the newly revamped straitstim­es.com, or download our mobile app today! str.sg/JaLa by Jan 10, 7pm Selected questions will be addressed and included in the video ’’ Jonathan Roberts Creative Director English, Malay, Tamil Media Video Mark your calendar and watch the video on Friday, Jan 29, 7pm www.straitstim­es.com The Straits Times www.facebook.com/ TheStraits­Times PRINTED AND DISTRIBUTE­D BY PRESSREADE­R PressReade­r.com +1 604 278 4604 ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY COPYRIGHT AND PROTECTED BY APPLICABLE LAW
